Incidence of Hand, Foot & Mouth Disease in Hong Kong 1994 to 2001
-----------------------------------------------------------------
The following background data on Coxsackie virus (CV) and Enterovirus 71
[EV] diagnoses in relation to hand, foot & mouth disease [HFMD] in Hong
Kong have been extracted from the GIDEON database.
Year/ Total HFMDV/ CV/ EV
1994/ 133/ 111/ 0
1995/ 71/ 36/ 1
1996/ 70/ 49/ 0
1997/ 64/ 30/ 2
1998/ 562/ 170/ 60
1999/ 347/ 214/ 22
2000/ 358/ 269/ 6
2001/ 284/ 230/ 30
In total, 477 patients were hospitalized for HFMD in 1999 (enterovirus 71
in 22 cases, 3 with neurological complications, 1 fatal); 111 patients in
2000 (enterovirus 71 in 6 cases, 1 fatal); and 114 patients in 2001 (none
with complications).
--
Dr. S. Berger
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
